                           "answer":"B)  Facebook’s stock is relatively liquid",
                           "explanation":"The size of an asset’s bid-ask spread is an indication of its <b>liquidity</b> or how easily an asset can be bought or sold in the market without impacting its price.  Currency, the most liquid asset in the world, has a bid-ask spread of one-hundredth of a percent while small-cap stocks can have bid-ask spreads of one or two percent.  Be careful about executing market orders for securities with large bid-ask spreads.  You could end up moving the market with your order and paying a high price as a result."
